The Ummah AI Initiative — Licensing

This repository currently contains documentation only. Future additions
will include source code, datasets, and other materials that may carry
different licenses. This file describes the licensing regime.

================================================================================

DOCUMENTATION
-------------

All documentation (.md files, written guides, diagrams in text form, and
similar written content) in this repository is licensed under the

    Creative Commons Attribution-ShareAlike 4.0 International License
    (CC BY-SA 4.0)

You are free to:

  • Share — copy and redistribute the material in any medium or format
  • Adapt — remix, transform, and build upon the material
    for any purpose, even commercially.

Under the following terms:

  • Attribution — You must give appropriate credit, provide a link to
    the license, and indicate if changes were made. You may do so in
    any reasonable manner, but not in any way that suggests the licensor
    endorses you or your use.

  • ShareAlike — If you remix, transform, or build upon the material,
    you must distribute your contributions under the same license as
    the original.

  • No additional restrictions — You may not apply legal terms or
    technological measures that legally restrict others from doing
    anything the license permits.

Full license text: https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-sa/4.0/legalcode

SPDX-License-Identifier: CC-BY-SA-4.0

================================================================================

CODE (future)
-------------

Source code added to this repository, and to projects released under
this initiative, will by default be licensed under the MIT License
unless a specific project file (e.g. a subdirectory LICENSE) specifies
otherwise.

Some components may be released under Apache License 2.0 where patent
grants are material. A small number of components may be released under
strong-copyleft terms (AGPL-3.0) where preventing proprietary
appropriation of defensive tooling is deemed essential. Such cases will
be clearly marked at their directory root.

Each source file or directory will either:

  (a) carry an SPDX-License-Identifier header, or
  (b) reside within a subtree with a clearly-marked LICENSE file.

In the absence of either marker, assume MIT.

================================================================================

DATA AND DATASETS (future)
--------------------------

Datasets released by this initiative will be licensed on a
dataset-by-dataset basis. Most public datasets will be released under
CC BY-SA 4.0 or CDLA-Sharing-1.0.

Datasets containing user data, activist data, or any content covered by
Layer 4 of the disclosure framework (see docs/03-open-vs-closed.md) will
NEVER be released publicly, under any license.

================================================================================

TRADEMARKS
----------

Names associated with the initiative and its projects — including but
not limited to "The Ummah AI Initiative", "Basira", "Shahid", "Hisn",
and "Mizan" — are reserved for use by the initiative itself. Third-party
use of these names in ways that suggest endorsement or official
affiliation is not permitted without written consent.

This restriction does NOT prevent:

  • Factual reference to the initiative or its projects in journalism,
    academic writing, or ordinary speech.
  • Forks of the code and documentation, provided the fork uses a
    different project name and does not misrepresent its relationship
    to the original.

================================================================================

CONTRIBUTOR AGREEMENTS
----------------------

By contributing to this repository, contributors agree that their
contributions will be licensed under the same terms that govern the
files they modify (typically CC BY-SA 4.0 for documentation, MIT for
code).

Contributors retain copyright in their contributions. No copyright
assignment is required. A Developer Certificate of Origin (DCO) may be
adopted for code contributions once a code phase begins.

================================================================================

QUESTIONS
---------

License questions may be raised as public issues in this repository. We
prefer open discussion over private correspondence on licensing matters.

================================================================================

This licensing regime is itself subject to the initiative's principles.
It may be updated through the governance process described in
docs/06-governance.md. Updates will not retroactively change the license
of previously-released content.
